## ITERATION 45 BODY

title: "045 — Marker Visual Cost + Zoom-Level Optimization"
description: "Reduce DOM, paint, and animation cost for vehicle markers and related map visuals while preserving readability."

:::GOALS

Lower the rendering cost of custom vehicle markers and map visuals.

Ensure markers remain readable while becoming cheaper to render.

Introduce zoom-aware marker detail so far zoom levels render less expensive markers.

:::END

:::TASKS

Audit `VehicleMarker` markup and remove unnecessary wrapper elements.

Keep the marker DOM structure as lean as possible while preserving the current design hierarchy.

Reduce expensive visual effects where they are not essential, including unnecessary layered shadows, glows, filters, or simultaneous animations.

Retain attention-grabbing effects only where they carry operational meaning, such as degraded or critical states.

Introduce zoom-based marker detail levels.

At minimum support:

- lower-detail marker presentation at farther zoom levels
- fuller marker presentation at closer zoom levels

Ensure far-zoom markers remain recognizable but cheaper to render.

Review route rendering styles relative to enlarged markers and keep route visibility balanced without excessive stroke cost.

Ensure event, alert, and camera overlays do not introduce unnecessary paint or layout cost while the map is moving.

Preserve current visual semantics and marker readability.

:::END

:::ACCEPTANCE

- Vehicle markers use a leaner DOM structure.
- Marker visuals cost less to render while remaining readable.
- Far-zoom marker rendering is simpler than near-zoom rendering.
- Map responsiveness improves without losing important operational cues.

:::END